simplifierConcept:
IF gives you one choice. But what about alternatives?

üå¶Ô∏è IF raining ‚Üí Umbrella
‚òÄÔ∏è ELSE ‚Üí Sunglasses

Two paths, pick one!

if (condition)
{
    // Path A: When TRUE
}
else
{
    // Path B: When FALSE
}

Multiple choices? Use ELSE IF:

üéì IF score >= 90 ‚Üí A
üìö ELSE IF score >= 80 ‚Üí B
üìñ ELSE IF score >= 70 ‚Üí C
üìù ELSE ‚Üí F

Only ONE path executes!

Think: if/else if/else creates a decision tree with multiple branches!

coderExample:
// BASIC IF-ELSE
int age = 16;

if (age >= 18)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Adult");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Minor");
}
// Prints "Minor" because condition false

// ELSE IF - Multiple conditions
int score = 85;

if (score >= 90)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Grade: A");
}
else if (score >= 80)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Grade: B");  // This runs!
}
else if (score >= 70)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Grade: C");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Grade: F");
}

